01:39:41,200 --> 01:39:43,200
A gift to the foes of Mordor.

978
01:39:43,900 --> 01:39:45,900
Why not use this Ring?

979
01:39:46,200 --> 01:39:48,900
Long has my father,
the Steward of Gondor...

980
01:39:49,200 --> 01:39:53,300
...kept the forces of Mordor at bay.
By the blood of our people...

981
01:39:53,800 --> 01:39:55,900
...are your lands kept safe.

982
01:39:57,800 --> 01:40:02,000
Give Gondor the weapon of the enemy.
Let us use it against him.

983
01:40:02,400 --> 01:40:06,000
You cannot wield it.
None of us can.

984
01:40:06,700 --> 01:40:10,600
The One Ring answers to Sauron alone.
It has no other master.

985
01:40:11,000 --> 01:40:14,400
And what would a Ranger know
of this matter?

986
01:40:14,900 --> 01:40:16,800
This is no mere Ranger.

987
01:40:17,800 --> 01:40:21,300
He is Aragorn, son of Arathorn.

988
01:40:22,000 --> 01:40:24,800
You owe him your allegiance.

989
01:40:28,900 --> 01:40:30,800
Aragorn.

990
01:40:32,700 --> 01:40:35,400
This is Isildur's heir?

991
01:40:37,800 --> 01:40:40,400
And heir to the throne of Gondor.

992
01:40:42,700 --> 01:40:44,100
Sit down, Legolas.

993
01:40:42,700 --> 01:40:44,100
Sit down, Legolas.

994
01:40:47,500 --> 01:40:50,200
Gondor has no king.

995
01:40:52,200 --> 01:40:53,800
Gondor needs no king.

996
01:41:00,500 --> 01:41:04,000
Aragorn is right. We cannot use it.

997
01:41:05,200 --> 01:41:08,500
You have only one choice.

998
01:41:09,000 --> 01:41:11,200
The Ring must be destroyed.

999
01:41:16,500 --> 01:41:19,000
What are we waiting for?

1000
01:41:31,200 --> 01:41:34,100
The Ring cannot be destroyed, Gimli,
son of Glin...

1001
01:41:34,400 --> 01:41:38,500
...by any craft that we here possess.

1002
01:41:39,200 --> 01:41:43,100
The Ring was made in the fires
of Mount Doom.

1003
01:41:43,600 --> 01:41:47,200
Only there can it be unmade.

1004
01:41:48,500 --> 01:41:50,900
It must be taken deep into Mordor...

1005
01:41:51,300 --> 01:41:56,000
...and cast back into the fiery chasm
from whence it came.

1006
01:41:58,200 --> 01:42:00,100
One of you...

1007
01:42:00,700 --> 01:42:02,800
...must do this.

1008
01:42:05,800 --> 01:42:09,400
One does not simply walk into Mordor.

1009
01:42:10,500 --> 01:42:13,900
Its Black Gates are guarded
by more than just Orcs.

1010
01:42:14,900 --> 01:42:18,900
There is evil there
that does not sleep.

1011
01:42:19,200 --> 01:42:23,300
The Great Eye is ever-watchful.

1012
01:42:24,200 --> 01:42:26,100
It is a barren wasteland...

1013
01:42:26,500 --> 01:42:29,900
...riddled with fire, and ash
and dust.

1014
01:42:30,300 --> 01:42:34,000
The very air you breathe
is a poisonous fume.

1015
01:42:34,400 --> 01:42:38,500
Not with 10,000 men
could you do this. It is folly.

1016
01:42:38,800 --> 01:42:43,100
Have you heard nothing Lord Elrond
has said? The Ring must be destroyed.

1017
01:42:43,500 --> 01:42:45,900
And I suppose you think
you are the one to do it!

1018
01:42:46,300 --> 01:42:50,700
And if we fail, what then? What happens
when Sauron takes back what is his?

1019
01:42:51,100 --> 01:42:56,200
I will be dead before I see the Ring
in the hands of an Elf!

1020
01:42:58,400 --> 01:43:00,800
Never trust an Elf!

1021
01:43:02,100 --> 01:43:07,700
Do you not understand? While you bicker
amongst yourselves, Sauron's power grows!

1022
01:43:08,200 --> 01:43:11,000
None can escape it!
You'll all be destroyed!

1023
01:43:29,900 --> 01:43:32,000
I will take it.

1024
01:43:34,100 --> 01:43:36,600
I will take it.

1025
01:43:42,400 --> 01:43:45,400
I will take the Ring to Mordor.

1026
01:43:53,700 --> 01:43:54,800
Though...

1027
01:43:58,100 --> 01:43:59,800
...I do not know the way.

1028
01:44:01,800 --> 01:44:05,900
I will help you bear
this burden, Frodo Baggins...

1029
01:44:06,400 --> 01:44:09,600
...as long as it is yours to bear.

1030
01:44:10,900 --> 01:44:13,800
If by my life
or death I can protect you...

1031
01:44:14,700 --> 01:44:16,000
...I will.

1032
01:44:19,200 --> 01:44:21,400
You have my sword.

1033
01:44:23,300 --> 01:44:25,300
And you have my bow.

1034
01:44:26,000 --> 01:44:28,400
And my ax.

1035
01:44:35,500 --> 01:44:38,400
You carry the fates
of us all, little one.

1036
01:44:40,500 --> 01:44:44,000
If this is indeed
the will of the Council...

1037
01:44:44,700 --> 01:44:47,000
...then Gondor will see it done.

1038
01:44:49,700 --> 01:44:54,300
- Frodo's not going anywhere without me.
- It is hardly possible to separate you...

1039
01:44:54,700 --> 01:44:59,300
...even when he is summoned
to a secret Council and you are not.

1040
01:45:00,100 --> 01:45:01,900
We're coming too!

1041
01:45:04,100 --> 01:45:06,700
You'll have to send us home
tied up in a sack to stop us.

1042
01:45:07,100 --> 01:45:10,300
Anyway, you need people
of intelligence on this sort of...

1043
01:45:10,700 --> 01:45:11,900
...mission.

1044
01:45:12,300 --> 01:45:13,600
Quest.

1045
01:45:14,200 --> 01:45:15,200
Thing.

1046
01:45:17,100 --> 01:45:19,700
Well, that rules you out, Pip.

1047
01:45:21,400 --> 01:45:23,200
Nine companions.

1048
01:45:25,000 --> 01:45:26,800
So be it.

1049
01:45:27,200 --> 01:45:30,100
You shall be
the Fellowship of the Ring.

1050
01:45:30,900 --> 01:45:32,700
Great!

1051
01:45:33,100 --> 01:45:35,300
Where are we going?

1052
01:46:11,000 --> 01:46:13,400
She wanted to protect her child...

1053
01:46:15,300 --> 01:46:18,900
she thought in Rivendell
you would be safe.

1054
01:46:21,300 --> 01:46:24,600
In her heart, your mother knew
you'd be hunted all your life.

1055
01:46:25,200 --> 01:46:26,800
That you'd never escape your fate.

1056
01:46:27,500 --> 01:46:30,900
The skill of the Elves
can reforge the sword of kings...

1057
01:46:31,500 --> 01:46:35,300
...but only you have the power
to wield it.

1058
01:46:36,500 --> 01:46:38,800
I do not want that power.

1059
01:46:39,100 --> 01:46:41,700
I have never wanted it.

1060
01:46:43,200 --> 01:46:45,600
You are the last of that bloodline.
There is no other.

1061
01:46:50,300 --> 01:46:52,500
My old sword! Sting.

1062
01:46:52,800 --> 01:46:53,900
Here, take it. Take it.

1063
01:46:59,400 --> 01:47:03,100
- It's so light.
- Yes. Made by the Elves, you know.

1064
01:47:04,000 --> 01:47:08,000
The blade glows blue
when Orcs are close.

1065
01:47:08,400 --> 01:47:12,800
And it's times like that, my lad,
when you have to be extra careful.

1066
01:47:13,200 --> 01:47:15,600
Here's a pretty thing.

1067
01:47:16,100 --> 01:47:17,300
Mithril.

1068
01:47:18,200 --> 01:47:22,400
As light as a feather,
and as hard as dragon scales.

1069
01:47:22,800 --> 01:47:25,900
Let me see you put it on. Come on.

1070
01:47:34,000 --> 01:47:36,000
My old ring.

1071
01:47:37,400 --> 01:47:41,100
I should very much like...

1072
01:47:41,500 --> 01:47:45,300
...to hold it again, one last time.

1073
01:48:02,900 --> 01:48:06,400
I'm sorry I brought this upon you,
my boy.

1074
01:48:06,900 --> 01:48:10,800
I'm sorry that you
must carry this burden.

1075
01:48:15,500 --> 01:48:18,400
I'm sorry for everything.

1076
01:48:33,400 --> 01:48:37,600
The Ring-bearer is setting out
on the Quest of Mount Doom.

1077
01:48:39,100 --> 01:48:41,600
On you who travel with him,
no oath...

1078
01:48:41,900 --> 01:48:44,900
...nor bond is laid to go further
than you will.

1079
01:48:48,500 --> 01:48:50,900
Farewell. Hold to your purpose.

1080
01:48:51,500 --> 01:48:55,200
May the blessings of Elves and Men...

1081
01:48:56,000 --> 01:48:58,500
...and all Free Folk go with you.

1082
01:49:01,600 --> 01:49:05,500
The Fellowship awaits the Ring-bearer.

1083
01:49:24,100 --> 01:49:26,500
Mordor, Gandalf, is it left or right?

1084
01:49:27,200 --> 01:49:29,000
Left.

1085
01:50:48,600 --> 01:50:52,900
<i>We must hold to this course, west</i>
<i>of the Misty Mountains, for 40 days.</i>

1086
01:50:53,300 --> 01:50:56,900
<i>If our luck holds, the Gap of Rohan</i>
<i>will still be open to us.</i>

1087
01:50:57,200 --> 01:51:00,600
<i>From there, our road</i>
<i>turns east to Mordor.</i>

1088
01:51:01,000 --> 01:51:04,600
Two, one, five. Good! Very good.

1089
01:51:06,600 --> 01:51:07,600
Move your feet.

1090
01:51:07,900 --> 01:51:09,100
- You look good, Pippin.
- Thanks.

1091
01:51:09,400 --> 01:51:10,700
Faster!

1092
01:51:12,100 --> 01:51:15,700
If anyone was to ask for my opinion,
which I note they're not...

1093
01:51:16,100 --> 01:51:18,800
...I'd say we were taking
the long way 'round.

1094
01:51:19,400 --> 01:51:22,300
Gandalf, we could pass through
the Mines of Moria.

1095
01:51:23,100 --> 01:51:26,800
My cousin Balin would give us
a royal welcome.

1096
01:51:27,100 --> 01:51:32,300
No, I would not take the road through
Moria unless I had no other choice.

1097
01:51:41,700 --> 01:51:42,800
Sorry!

1098
01:51:43,600 --> 01:51:45,100
Get him!

1099
01:51:46,600 --> 01:51:48,900
- For the Shire!
- Hold him. Hold him down, Merry!

1100
01:51:49,700 --> 01:51:51,900
Gentlemen, that's enough.

1101
01:51:55,700 --> 01:51:57,300
You've got my arm!
You've got my arm!

1102
01:51:57,800 --> 01:52:00,300
- What is that?
- Nothing. It's just a wisp of cloud.

1103
01:52:00,700 --> 01:52:03,200
It's moving fast.

1104
01:52:03,600 --> 01:52:05,700
Against the wind.

1105
01:52:06,600 --> 01:52:08,600
- Crebain from Dunland!
- Hide!

1106
01:52:08,800 --> 01:52:11,500
- Hurry!
- Take cover!

1107
01:52:45,000 --> 01:52:46,600
Spies of Saruman.

1108
01:52:47,500 --> 01:52:50,600
The passage south is being watched.

1109
01:52:51,900 --> 01:52:55,100
We must take the Pass of Caradhras.

1110
01:53:07,900 --> 01:53:09,600
Frodo!

1111
01:53:28,600 --> 01:53:30,800
Boromir.

1112
01:53:31,100 --> 01:53:35,100
It is a strange fate that we should
suffer so much fear and doubt...

1113
01:53:35,500 --> 01:53:38,500
...over so small a thing.

1114
01:53:41,800 --> 01:53:43,700
Such a little thing.

1115
01:53:44,000 --> 01:53:45,400
Boromir!

1116
01:53:46,100 --> 01:53:48,600
Give the Ring to Frodo.

1117
01:53:58,600 --> 01:54:00,500
As you wish.

1118
01:54:01,300 --> 01:54:03,300
I care not.

1119
01:54:38,800 --> 01:54:43,300
So, Gandalf, you try
to lead them over Caradhras.

1120
01:54:43,700 --> 01:54:48,100
And if that fails,
where then will you go?

1121
01:54:49,600 --> 01:54:52,400
<i>If the mountain defeats you...</i>

1122
01:54:52,700 --> 01:54:57,000
<i>...will you risk</i>
<i>a more dangerous road?</i>

1123
01:55:09,500 --> 01:55:12,300
There is a fell voice on the air.

1124
01:55:13,600 --> 01:55:15,000
It's Saruman!

1125
01:55:24,000 --> 01:55:28,400
He's trying to bring down the mountain!
Gandalf, we must turn back!

1126
01:55:28,800 --> 01:55:30,600
No!

1127
01:56:37,100 --> 01:56:38,900
We must get off the mountain!

1128
01:56:39,400 --> 01:56:43,600
Make for the Gap of Rohan,
and take the west road to my city!

1129
01:56:44,000 --> 01:56:47,200
The Gap of Rohan takes us
too close to Isengard!

1130
01:56:47,500 --> 01:56:51,100
We cannot pass over a mountain.
Let us go under it.

1131
01:56:51,500 --> 01:56:54,200
Let us go through the Mines of Moria.

1132
01:56:56,200 --> 01:56:59,800
<i>Moria. You fear to go</i>
<i>into those mines.</i>

1133
01:57:00,600 --> 01:57:05,400
The Dwarves delved too greedily
and too deep.

1134
01:57:06,500 --> 01:57:11,100
<i>You know what they awoke</i>
<i>in the darkness of Khazad-dm:</i>

1135
01:57:12,600 --> 01:57:15,900
Shadow and flame.

1136
01:57:19,500 --> 01:57:22,100
Let the Ring-bearer decide.

1137
01:57:26,900 --> 01:57:28,900
We cannot stay here!

1138
01:57:29,200 --> 01:57:31,800
This will be the death of the Hobbits.

1139
01:57:32,200 --> 01:57:33,700
Frodo?

1140
01:57:36,900 --> 01:57:39,600
We will go through the mines.

1141
01:57:40,600 --> 01:57:42,400
So be it.

1142
01:57:49,100 --> 01:57:52,800
Frodo, come and help an old man.

1143
01:57:56,500 --> 01:57:58,600
How is your shoulder?

1144
01:57:58,900 --> 01:58:02,000
- Better than it was.
- And the Ring?

1145
01:58:03,700 --> 01:58:06,100
You feel its power growing, don't you?

1146
01:58:06,700 --> 01:58:09,500
I've felt it too.
You must be careful now.

1147
01:58:10,100 --> 01:58:13,800
Evil will be drawn to you
from outside the Fellowship.

1148
01:58:14,100 --> 01:58:16,600
And, I fear, from within.

1149
01:58:19,400 --> 01:58:23,300
- Who then do I trust?
- You must trust yourself.

1150
01:58:23,700 --> 01:58:26,400
Trust your own strengths.

1151
01:58:26,800 --> 01:58:29,200
- What do you mean?
- There are many powers in this world...

1152
01:58:29,500 --> 01:58:31,500
...for good or for evil.

1153
01:58:31,800 --> 01:58:34,000
Some are greater than I am.

1154
01:58:34,600 --> 01:58:38,100
And against some I have not yet
been tested.

1155
01:58:39,600 --> 01:58:40,900
The walls...

1156
01:58:41,700 --> 01:58:43,700
...of Moria.

1157
01:58:49,500 --> 01:58:52,300
Dwarf doors are invisible when closed.

1158
01:58:52,700 --> 01:58:56,900
Yes, Gimli, their own masters cannot find
them if their secrets are forgotten.

1159
01:58:57,500 --> 01:58:59,800
Why doesn't that surprise me?

1160
01:59:07,900 --> 01:59:11,100
Well, let's see.

1161
01:59:11,500 --> 01:59:12,800
Ithildin.

1162
01:59:13,600 --> 01:59:16,800
It mirrors only starlight
and moonlight.

1163
01:59:31,000 --> 01:59:34,900
It reads, "The Doors of Durin,
Lord of Moria.

1164
01:59:35,700 --> 01:59:40,100
- Speak, friend, and enter."
- What do you suppose that means?

1165
01:59:40,500 --> 01:59:45,000
It's simple. If you are a friend, you speak
the password and the doors will open.

1166
02:00:09,000 --> 02:00:10,000
Nothing's happening.

1167
02:00:17,200 --> 02:00:21,200
I once knew every spell
in all the tongues of Elves...

1168
02:00:21,600 --> 02:00:24,200
...Men and Orcs.

1169
02:00:24,700 --> 02:00:25,900
What are you going to do, then?

1170
02:00:26,100 --> 02:00:28,200
Knock your head against these doors,
Peregrin Took!

1171
02:00:28,600 --> 02:00:30,500
And if that does not shatter them...

1172
02:00:30,800 --> 02:00:33,300
...and I am allowed a little peace
from foolish questions...

1173
02:00:33,600 --> 02:00:36,900
...I will try to find the opening words.

1174
02:00:50,000 --> 02:00:52,400
Mines are no place for a pony.

1175
02:00:52,800 --> 02:00:56,700
- Even one so brave as Bill.
- Bye-bye, Bill.

1176
02:00:58,000 --> 02:01:00,700
Go on, Bill. Go on.

1177
02:01:01,400 --> 02:01:04,800
Don't worry, Sam,
he knows the way home.

1178
02:01:11,800 --> 02:01:14,200
Do not disturb the water.

1179
02:01:14,500 --> 02:01:16,300
Oh, it's useless.

1180
02:01:29,100 --> 02:01:31,200
It's a riddle.

1181
02:01:34,000 --> 02:01:37,000
"Speak 'friend' and enter."

1182
02:01:37,500 --> 02:01:40,300
What's the Elvish word for "friend"?

1183
02:01:41,800 --> 02:01:43,100
<i>Mellon.</i>

1184
02:02:01,200 --> 02:02:05,900
Soon, Master Elf, you will enjoy
the fabled hospitality of the Dwarves.

1185
02:02:06,500 --> 02:02:12,000
Roaring fires, malt beer,
ripe meat off the bone!

1186
02:02:13,700 --> 02:02:16,700
This, my friend,
is the home of my cousin Balin.

1187
02:02:17,200 --> 02:02:19,500
And they call it a mine.

1188
02:02:19,800 --> 02:02:21,700
A mine!

1189
02:02:22,800 --> 02:02:26,000
This is no mine. It's a tomb.

1190
02:02:32,300 --> 02:02:33,800
No...

1191
02:02:35,100 --> 02:02:36,700
No!

1192
02:02:39,400 --> 02:02:40,900
Goblins.

1193
02:02:44,900 --> 02:02:49,000
We make for the Gap of Rohan.
We should never have come here.

1194
02:02:50,200 --> 02:02:52,700
Now, get out of here. Get out!

1195
02:02:55,600 --> 02:02:57,800
- Frodo!
- Help!

1196
02:02:58,100 --> 02:02:59,600
Strider!

1197
02:03:00,000 --> 02:03:02,600
- Help!
- Get off him!

1198
02:03:02,900 --> 02:03:03,900
Aragorn!

1199
02:03:14,400 --> 02:03:15,400
Frodo!

1200
02:03:41,700 --> 02:03:42,700
Into the mines!

1201
02:03:42,900 --> 02:03:46,000
- Legolas!
- Into the cave!

1202
02:03:50,500 --> 02:03:52,200
Run!

1203
02:04:09,100 --> 02:04:12,500
We now have but one choice.

1204
02:04:13,000 --> 02:04:17,600
We must face the long dark of Moria.

1205
02:04:18,100 --> 02:04:19,900
Be on your guard.

1206
02:04:20,300 --> 02:04:23,500
There are older
and fouler things than Orcs...

1207
02:04:23,800 --> 02:04:27,200
...in the deep places of the world.

1208
02:04:35,400 --> 02:04:39,100
Quietly now. It's a four-day journey
to the other side.

1209
02:04:39,500 --> 02:04:43,200
Let us hope that our presence
may go unnoticed.

1210
02:05:29,100 --> 02:05:32,600
The wealth of Moria was not in gold...

1211
02:05:33,000 --> 02:05:35,200
...or jewels...

1212
02:05:35,500 --> 02:05:38,400
...but mithril.

1213
02:05:57,000 --> 02:06:01,600
Bilbo had a shirt of mithril rings
that Thorin gave him.

1214
02:06:02,100 --> 02:06:05,800
- Oh, that was a kingly gift.
- Yes.

1215
02:06:06,200 --> 02:06:08,000
I never told him...

1216
02:06:08,300 --> 02:06:13,100
...but its worth was greater than
the value of the Shire.

1217
02:06:25,600 --> 02:06:27,300
Pippin.

1218
02:06:47,700 --> 02:06:50,500
I have no memory of this place.

1219
02:06:52,700 --> 02:06:54,000
- Are we lost?
- No.

1220
02:06:54,400 --> 02:06:56,800
- I think we are.
- Gandalf's thinking.

1221
02:06:57,100 --> 02:06:58,500
- Merry?
- What?

1222
02:06:58,700 --> 02:07:00,500
I'm hungry.

1223
02:07:12,000 --> 02:07:16,300
- There's something down there.
- It's Gollum.

1224
02:07:16,700 --> 02:07:20,600
- Gollum?
- He's been following us for three days.

1225
02:07:21,000 --> 02:07:24,900
- He escaped the dungeons of Barad-dr?
- Escaped...

1226
02:07:25,800 --> 02:07:27,400
...or was set loose.

1227
02:07:28,000 --> 02:07:31,500
Now the Ring has brought him here.

1228
02:07:34,300 --> 02:07:36,900
He will never be rid of his need for it.

1229
02:07:37,300 --> 02:07:42,700
He hates and loves the Ring,
as he hates and loves himself.

1230
02:07:43,100 --> 02:07:47,700
Smagol's life is a sad story.

1231
02:07:48,100 --> 02:07:53,800
Yes, Smagol he was once called.
Before the Ring found him.

1232
02:07:55,100 --> 02:07:57,700
Before it drove him mad.

1233
02:07:58,200 --> 02:08:00,900
It's a pity Bilbo didn't kill him
when he had the chance.

1234
02:08:01,300 --> 02:08:02,400
Pity?

1235
02:08:03,500 --> 02:08:06,300
It is pity that stayed Bilbo's hand.

1236
02:08:07,300 --> 02:08:12,300
Many that live deserve death.
Some that die deserve life.

1237
02:08:14,000 --> 02:08:16,300
Can you give it to them, Frodo?

1238
02:08:18,900 --> 02:08:22,700
Do not be too eager
to deal out death and judgment.

1239
02:08:23,100 --> 02:08:25,900
Even the very wise
cannot see all ends.

1240
02:08:26,500 --> 02:08:32,200
My heart tells me that Gollum has some
part to play yet, for good or ill...

1241
02:08:33,300 --> 02:08:36,000
...before this is over.

1242
02:08:37,700 --> 02:08:41,300
The pity of Bilbo
may rule the fate of many.

1243
02:08:48,200 --> 02:08:51,300
I wish the Ring
had never come to me.

1244
02:08:52,900 --> 02:08:54,900
I wish none of this had happened.

1245
02:08:55,200 --> 02:09:00,000
So do all who live to see such times.
But that is not for them to decide.

1246
02:09:01,000 --> 02:09:06,200
All we have to decide is what to do
with the time that is given to us.

1247
02:09:08,000 --> 02:09:11,800
There are other forces at work in this
world, Frodo, besides the will of evil.

1248
02:09:12,400 --> 02:09:14,700
Bilbo was meant to find the Ring.

1249
02:09:15,300 --> 02:09:19,400
In which case,
you also were meant to have it.

1250
02:09:19,900 --> 02:09:22,900
And that is an encouraging thought.

1251
02:09:27,900 --> 02:09:29,700
It's that way.

1252
02:09:30,000 --> 02:09:32,200
- He's remembered.
- No.

1253
02:09:32,500 --> 02:09:36,100
But the air doesn't smell
so foul down here.

1254
02:09:36,600 --> 02:09:41,500
If in doubt, Meriadoc,
always follow your nose.

1255
02:09:56,600 --> 02:10:00,500
Let me risk a little more light.

1256
02:10:05,300 --> 02:10:07,300
Behold...

1257
02:10:07,800 --> 02:10:12,800
...the great realm
and Dwarf-city of Dwarrowdelf.

1258
02:10:15,600 --> 02:10:18,900
There's an eye opener, and no mistake.

1259
02:10:43,900 --> 02:10:45,500
Gimli!

1260
02:10:53,100 --> 02:10:54,600
No!

1261
02:10:57,300 --> 02:11:00,300
Oh, no.

1262
02:11:02,300 --> 02:11:03,500
No.

1263
02:11:10,800 --> 02:11:12,700
"Here lies Balin...

1264
02:11:13,300 --> 02:11:15,200
...son of Fundin...

1265
02:11:15,600 --> 02:11:18,100
...Lord of Moria."

1266
02:11:19,300 --> 02:11:20,900
He is dead, then.

1267
02:11:22,700 --> 02:11:24,300
It's as I feared.

1268
02:11:42,600 --> 02:11:45,400
We must move on. We cannot linger.

1269
02:11:45,700 --> 02:11:50,200
"They have taken the bridge
and the second hall.

1270
02:11:51,500 --> 02:11:54,000
We have barred the gates...

1271
02:11:54,800 --> 02:11:57,100
...but cannot hold them for long.

1272
02:11:57,400 --> 02:12:00,100
The ground shakes.

1273
02:12:00,600 --> 02:12:02,100
Drums...

1274
02:12:02,600 --> 02:12:05,800
...drums in the deep.

1275
02:12:09,600 --> 02:12:11,500
We cannot get out.

1276
02:12:13,600 --> 02:12:17,300
A Shadow moves in the dark.

1277
02:12:19,100 --> 02:12:21,600
We cannot get out.

1278
02:12:24,700 --> 02:12:26,500
They are coming."

1279
02:13:09,700 --> 02:13:11,400
Fool of a Took!

1280
02:13:11,800 --> 02:13:15,400
Throw yourself in next time,
and rid us of your stupidity.

1281
02:13:41,700 --> 02:13:43,300
Frodo!

1282
02:13:45,700 --> 02:13:47,000
Orcs.

1283
02:13:54,200 --> 02:13:56,100
Get back! Stay close to Gandalf!

1284
02:14:03,300 --> 02:14:05,100
They have a cave-troll.

1285
02:14:21,000 --> 02:14:22,100
Let them come!

1286
02:14:22,600 --> 02:14:26,000
There is one Dwarf yet in Moria
who still draws breath.

1287
02:16:45,300 --> 02:16:48,000
I think I'm getting the hang of this.

1288
02:16:52,800 --> 02:16:54,500
Frodo!

1289
02:17:28,100 --> 02:17:29,900
Aragorn! Aragorn!

1290
02:17:31,000 --> 02:17:32,800
Frodo!

1291
02:18:18,000 --> 02:18:19,800
Frodo!

1292
02:19:20,200 --> 02:19:21,400
Oh, no.

1293
02:19:29,800 --> 02:19:31,600
He's alive.

1294
02:19:34,200 --> 02:19:37,000
I'm all right. I'm not hurt.

1295
02:19:37,400 --> 02:19:39,500
You should be dead.

1296
02:19:39,800 --> 02:19:42,200
That spear would have skewered
a wild boar.

1297
02:19:42,500 --> 02:19:47,100
I think there's more to this Hobbit
than meets the eye.

1298
02:19:53,100 --> 02:19:54,100
Mithril.

1299
02:19:57,000 --> 02:19:59,500
You are full of surprises,
Master Baggins.

1300
02:20:05,600 --> 02:20:07,400
To the Bridge of Khazad-dm!

1301
02:20:22,600 --> 02:20:24,100
This way!

1302
02:21:34,500 --> 02:21:37,400
What is this new devilry?

1303
02:21:53,600 --> 02:21:56,300
A Balrog.

1304
02:21:56,700 --> 02:21:59,700
A demon of the ancient world.

1305
02:22:02,100 --> 02:22:04,400
This foe is beyond any of you.

1306
02:22:05,700 --> 02:22:07,200
Run!

1307
02:22:14,600 --> 02:22:16,100
Quickly!

1308
02:22:32,700 --> 02:22:33,900
Gandalf.

1309
02:22:34,600 --> 02:22:36,100
Lead them on, Aragorn.

1310
02:22:37,600 --> 02:22:40,000
The bridge is near.

1311
02:22:42,200 --> 02:22:46,100
Do as I say!
Swords are no more use here.

1312
02:23:15,400 --> 02:23:17,000
Gandalf!

1313
02:23:35,500 --> 02:23:36,600
Merry! Pippin!

1314
02:23:47,800 --> 02:23:49,300
Sam!

1315
02:23:52,000 --> 02:23:55,100
Nobody tosses a Dwarf.

1316
02:23:58,300 --> 02:23:59,700
Not the beard!

1317
02:24:13,000 --> 02:24:14,800
Steady.

1318
02:24:17,000 --> 02:24:18,600
Hold on!

1319
02:24:39,700 --> 02:24:40,800
Hang on!

1320
02:24:51,700 --> 02:24:53,300
Lean forward!

1321
02:24:56,400 --> 02:24:57,400
Steady.

1322
02:24:58,800 --> 02:24:59,900
Come on!

1323
02:25:00,100 --> 02:25:01,500
Now!

1324
02:25:18,800 --> 02:25:20,600
Over the bridge!

1325
02:25:20,900 --> 02:25:22,400
Fly!

1326
02:26:07,000 --> 02:26:08,900
You cannot pass!

1327
02:26:09,200 --> 02:26:10,700
Gandalf!

1328
02:26:15,100 --> 02:26:19,800
I am a servant of the Secret Fire,
wielder of the flame of Anor.

1329
02:26:21,000 --> 02:26:24,600
The dark fire will not avail you,
flame of Udn!

1330
02:26:34,800 --> 02:26:36,600
Go back to the Shadow.

1331
02:26:44,600 --> 02:26:48,800
You shall not pass!

1332
02:27:16,200 --> 02:27:19,900
- No! No!
- Gandalf!

1333
02:27:27,700 --> 02:27:30,000
Fly, you fools!

1334
02:27:34,300 --> 02:27:36,300
No!

1335
02:27:42,500 --> 02:27:44,600
Aragorn!

1336
02:28:42,100 --> 02:28:44,700
Legolas, get them up.

1337
02:28:48,900 --> 02:28:50,700
Give them a moment, for pity's sake!

1338
02:28:51,000 --> 02:28:54,400
By nightfall, these hills will
be swarming with Orcs.

1339
02:28:54,900 --> 02:28:58,000
We must reach the woods of Lothlrien.

1340
02:28:59,100 --> 02:29:02,300
Come, Boromir. Legolas.
Gimli, get them up.

1341
02:29:03,900 --> 02:29:06,000
On your feet, Sam.

1342
02:29:06,500 --> 02:29:07,900
Frodo?

1343
02:29:10,000 --> 02:29:11,600
Frodo!

1344
02:30:04,200 --> 02:30:06,600
Stay close, young Hobbits!

1345
02:30:07,400 --> 02:30:11,400
They say that a great sorceress
lives in these woods.

1346
02:30:11,800 --> 02:30:14,200
An Elf-witch...

1347
02:30:15,000 --> 02:30:17,700
...of terrible power.

1348
02:30:18,300 --> 02:30:20,400
All who look upon her...

1349
02:30:20,800 --> 02:30:22,500
...fall under her spell.

1350
02:30:22,800 --> 02:30:24,000
<i>Frodo!</i>

1351
02:30:26,300 --> 02:30:28,200
And are never seen again.

1352
02:30:28,500 --> 02:30:32,800
<i>Your coming to us is</i>
<i>as the footsteps of doom.</i>

1353
02:30:33,300 --> 02:30:36,800
<i>You bring great evil here,</i>
<i>Ring-bearer.</i>

1354
02:30:37,200 --> 02:30:38,900
Mr. Frodo?

1355
02:30:44,300 --> 02:30:49,600
Well, here's one Dwarf
she won't ensnare so easily.

1356
02:30:50,000 --> 02:30:54,400
I have the eyes of a hawk
and the ears of a fox.

1357
02:31:02,300 --> 02:31:06,600
The Dwarf breathes so loud,
we could have shot him in the dark.

1358
02:31:12,000 --> 02:31:13,900
Welcome Legolas, son of Thranduil.

1359
02:31:14,900 --> 02:31:17,400
Our Fellowship stands in your debt.

1360
02:31:20,300 --> 02:31:21,900
Aragorn of the Dunedain...

1361
02:31:22,700 --> 02:31:24,000
you are known to us.

1362
02:31:25,000 --> 02:31:27,100
So much for the legendary courtesy
of the Elves!

1363
02:31:27,400 --> 02:31:29,200
Speak words we can all understand!

1364
02:31:29,500 --> 02:31:33,900
We have not had dealings
with the Dwarves since the Dark Days.

1365
02:31:34,400 --> 02:31:36,800
And you know what this Dwarf
says to that?

1366
02:31:43,800 --> 02:31:45,600
That was not so courteous.

1367
02:31:52,200 --> 02:31:56,100
You bring great evil with you.

1368
02:31:58,100 --> 02:32:00,200
You can go no further.

1369
02:32:37,700 --> 02:32:40,200
Gandalf's death was not in vain.

1370
02:32:41,400 --> 02:32:43,200
Nor would he have you give up hope.

1371
02:32:44,900 --> 02:32:48,000
You carry a heavy burden, Frodo.

1372
02:32:49,000 --> 02:32:51,900
Don't carry the weight of the dead.

1373
02:32:55,000 --> 02:32:56,900
You will follow me.

1374
02:33:08,700 --> 02:33:10,500
Caras Galadhon.

1375
02:33:11,300 --> 02:33:14,000
The heart of Elvendom on earth.

1376
02:33:14,500 --> 02:33:19,900
Realm of the Lord Celeborn
and of Galadriel, Lady of Light.

1377
02:34:39,200 --> 02:34:42,100
The enemy knows you have entered here.

1378
02:34:43,000 --> 02:34:47,900
What hope you had in secrecy
is now gone.

1379
02:34:49,900 --> 02:34:54,100
Eight there are here, yet nine there
were set out from Rivendell.

1380
02:34:54,600 --> 02:34:56,300
Tell me, where is Gandalf?

1381
02:34:56,500 --> 02:34:59,500
For I much desire to speak with him.

1382
02:34:59,900 --> 02:35:02,500
I can no longer see him from afar.

1383
02:35:03,500 --> 02:35:08,400
Gandalf the Grey did not pass
the borders of this land.

1384
02:35:08,900 --> 02:35:11,200
He has fallen into Shadow.

1385
02:35:16,000 --> 02:35:20,300
He was taken by both Shadow and flame.

1386
02:35:22,300 --> 02:35:25,800
A Balrog of Morgoth.

1387
02:35:26,700 --> 02:35:29,900
For we went needlessly
into the net of Moria.

1388
02:35:32,200 --> 02:35:35,300
Needless were none of the deeds
of Gandalf in life.

1389
02:35:36,000 --> 02:35:39,100
We do not yet know his full purpose.

1390
02:35:44,100 --> 02:35:48,200
Do not let the great emptiness
of Khazad-dm fill your heart...

1391
02:35:48,600 --> 02:35:50,900
...Gimli, son of Glin.

1392
02:35:51,900 --> 02:35:55,300
For the world has grown
full of peril...

1393
02:35:56,900 --> 02:35:59,400
...and in all lands...

1394
02:35:59,800 --> 02:36:03,100
...Iove is now mingled with grief.

1395
02:36:15,900 --> 02:36:18,500
What now becomes of this Fellowship?

1396
02:36:19,200 --> 02:36:22,000
Without Gandalf, hope is lost.

1397
02:36:25,200 --> 02:36:28,300
The quest stands upon the edge
of a knife.

1398
02:36:28,600 --> 02:36:31,500
Stray but a little and it will fail...

1399
02:36:32,400 --> 02:36:35,100
...to the ruin of all.

1400
02:36:39,600 --> 02:36:45,100
Yet hope remains
while the Company is true.

1401
02:36:46,900 --> 02:36:51,500
Do not let your hearts be troubled.
Go now and rest...

1402
02:36:52,200 --> 02:36:55,700
...for you are weary with sorrow
and much toil.

1403
02:36:58,100 --> 02:37:00,100
Tonight, you will sleep...

1404
02:37:00,500 --> 02:37:03,800
<i>Welcome, Frodo of the Shire...</i>

1405
02:37:05,400 --> 02:37:07,100
<i>...one who has seen the Eye!</i>

1406
02:37:21,800 --> 02:37:24,300
A lament for Gandalf.

1407
02:37:31,700 --> 02:37:33,100
What do they say about him?

1408
02:37:33,400 --> 02:37:35,900
I have not the heart to tell you.

1409
02:37:39,000 --> 02:37:41,100
For me, the grief is still too near.

1410
02:37:44,200 --> 02:37:46,800
I bet they don't mention his fireworks.

1411
02:37:47,200 --> 02:37:50,100
There should be a verse about them.

1412
02:37:53,800 --> 02:37:55,700
<i>The finest rockets ever seen</i>

1413
02:37:56,900 --> 02:37:59,600
<i>They burst in stars of blue and green</i>

1414
02:38:00,600 --> 02:38:05,600
<i>Or after thunder, silver showers</i>

1415
02:38:06,600 --> 02:38:09,200
<i>Came falling like a rain of flowers</i>

1416
02:38:09,500 --> 02:38:13,200
Oh, that doesn't do them justice
by a long road.

1417
02:38:24,100 --> 02:38:26,700
Take some rest.

1418
02:38:27,000 --> 02:38:29,500
These borders are well-protected.

1419
02:38:29,800 --> 02:38:32,200
I will find no rest here.

1420
02:38:35,300 --> 02:38:38,100
I heard her voice inside my head.

1421
02:38:38,600 --> 02:38:42,000
She spoke of my father
and the fall of Gondor.

1422
02:38:42,500 --> 02:38:47,700
She said to me,
"Even now there is hope left."

1423
02:38:49,200 --> 02:38:51,900
But I cannot see it.

1424
02:38:53,400 --> 02:38:55,800
It is long since we had any hope.

1425
02:39:06,100 --> 02:39:08,100
My father is a noble man.

1426
02:39:09,000 --> 02:39:11,100
But his rule is failing...

1427
02:39:14,400 --> 02:39:16,900
...and our people lose faith.

1428
02:39:18,400 --> 02:39:21,700
He looks to me to make things right,
and I would do it.

1429
02:39:22,100 --> 02:39:25,500
I would see the glory
of Gondor restored.

1430
02:39:28,500 --> 02:39:31,300
Have you ever seen it, Aragorn?

1431
02:39:32,100 --> 02:39:34,000
The White Tower of Ecthelion.

1432
02:39:34,400 --> 02:39:38,000
Glimmering like a spike
of pearl and silver.

1433
02:39:38,900 --> 02:39:42,200
Its banners caught high
in the morning breeze.

1434
02:39:45,200 --> 02:39:47,100
Have you ever been called home...

1435
02:39:47,400 --> 02:39:51,100
...by the clear ringing
of silver trumpets?

1436
02:39:51,900 --> 02:39:55,000
I have seen the White City...

1437
02:39:55,500 --> 02:39:56,900
...Iong ago.

1438
02:39:57,900 --> 02:40:02,700
One day, our paths will lead us there.

1439
02:40:03,900 --> 02:40:06,700
And the tower guard
shall take up the call:

1440
02:40:07,300 --> 02:40:10,400
"The Lords of Gondor have returned."

1441
02:41:17,800 --> 02:41:20,200
Will you look into the mirror?

1442
02:41:20,500 --> 02:41:22,000
What will I see?

1443
02:41:25,000 --> 02:41:27,200
Even the wisest cannot tell.

1444
02:41:28,200 --> 02:41:30,000
For the mirror...

1445
02:41:30,300 --> 02:41:32,700
...shows many things.

1446
02:41:35,800 --> 02:41:38,100
Things that were...

1447
02:41:38,400 --> 02:41:40,900
...things that are...

1448
02:41:41,800 --> 02:41:43,700
...and some things...

1449
02:41:47,300 --> 02:41:50,500
...that have not yet come to pass.

1450
02:43:13,200 --> 02:43:15,900
I know what it is you saw.

1451
02:43:18,500 --> 02:43:20,900
For it is also in my mind.

1452
02:43:22,800 --> 02:43:26,700
<i>It is what will come to pass</i>
<i>if you should fail.</i>

1453
02:43:29,200 --> 02:43:33,800
<i>The Fellowship is breaking.</i>
<i>It is already begun.</i>

1454
02:43:34,800 --> 02:43:37,900
<i>He will try to take the Ring.</i>

1455
02:43:38,200 --> 02:43:40,100
<i>You know of whom I speak.</i>

1456
02:43:41,200 --> 02:43:45,700
<i>One by one, it will destroy them all.</i>

1457
02:43:47,400 --> 02:43:49,800
<i>If you ask it of</i> me...

1458
02:43:50,200 --> 02:43:53,200
<i>...I will give you the One Ring.</i>

1459
02:43:54,400 --> 02:43:56,500
You offer it to me freely.

1460
02:44:01,100 --> 02:44:04,800
I do not deny that my heart
has greatly desired this.

1461
02:44:11,500 --> 02:44:14,600
In place of a Dark Lord,
you would have a queen...

1462
02:44:15,200 --> 02:44:18,800
...not dark but beautiful,
and terrible as the dawn!

1463
02:44:19,600 --> 02:44:22,500
Treacherous as the sea!

1464
02:44:23,100 --> 02:44:27,800
Stronger than the foundations
of the earth!

1465
02:44:28,600 --> 02:44:30,800
All shall love me...

1466
02:44:31,100 --> 02:44:33,800
...and despair.

1467
02:44:48,100 --> 02:44:52,200
I pass the test. I will diminish...

1468
02:44:52,600 --> 02:44:54,900
...and go into the West...

1469
02:44:55,300 --> 02:44:59,600
...and remain Galadriel.
- I cannot do this alone.

1470
02:45:03,400 --> 02:45:07,300
You are a Ring-bearer, Frodo.
To bear a Ring of Power...

1471
02:45:08,400 --> 02:45:09,900
...is to be alone.

1472
02:45:13,300 --> 02:45:15,900
This is Nenya,
the Ring of Adamant.

1473
02:45:16,200 --> 02:45:17,700
And I am its keeper.

1474
02:45:21,000 --> 02:45:24,500
This task was appointed to you.

1475
02:45:25,700 --> 02:45:28,400
And if you do not find a way...

1476
02:45:29,800 --> 02:45:31,700
...no one will.

1477
02:45:32,200 --> 02:45:35,200
Then I know what I must do.

1478
02:45:36,000 --> 02:45:37,100
It's just...

1479
02:45:40,500 --> 02:45:42,600
...I'm afraid to do it.

1480
02:45:46,200 --> 02:45:51,100
Even the smallest person can change
the course of the future.

1481
02:45:56,700 --> 02:46:02,200
Do you know how the Orcs
first came into being?

1482
02:46:03,200 --> 02:46:06,300
They were Elves once.

1483
02:46:07,700 --> 02:46:10,900
Taken by the Dark Powers...

1484
02:46:11,300 --> 02:46:14,300
...tortured and mutilated.

1485
02:46:14,700 --> 02:46:19,800
A ruined and terrible form of life.

1486
02:46:20,300 --> 02:46:22,000
And now...

1487
02:46:23,700 --> 02:46:25,400
...perfected.

1488
02:46:26,200 --> 02:46:29,300
My fighting Uruk-hai...

1489
02:46:31,400 --> 02:46:33,500
...whom do you serve?

1490
02:46:33,900 --> 02:46:36,200
Saruman!

1491
02:46:57,200 --> 02:47:00,400
Hunt them down. Do not stop
until they are found.

1492
02:47:00,800 --> 02:47:03,600
You do not know pain.
You do not know fear.

1493
02:47:03,900 --> 02:47:06,800
You will taste Man-flesh!

1494
02:47:12,200 --> 02:47:15,700
One of the halflings carries
something of great value.

1495
02:47:16,100 --> 02:47:20,200
Bring them to me alive and unspoiled.

1496
02:47:22,100 --> 02:47:23,300
Kill the others.

1497
02:47:42,600 --> 02:47:47,900
Never before have we clad strangers
in the garb of our own people.

1498
02:47:49,200 --> 02:47:52,800
May these cloaks help shield you
from unfriendly eyes.

1499
02:48:00,200 --> 02:48:01,800
Lembas.

1500
02:48:02,100 --> 02:48:03,600
Elvish waybread.

1501
02:48:06,100 --> 02:48:09,000
One small bite is enough to fill
the stomach of a grown man.

1502
02:48:15,600 --> 02:48:17,400
How many did you eat?

1503
02:48:17,800 --> 02:48:19,300
Four.

1504
02:48:25,200 --> 02:48:27,700
<i>Every league you travel south,</i>
<i>the danger will increase.</i>

1505
02:48:28,000 --> 02:48:31,900
<i>Mordor Orcs now hold the eastern shore</i>
<i>of the Anduin.</i>

1506
02:48:32,300 --> 02:48:34,700
<i>Nor will you find safety</i>
<i>on the western bank.</i>

1507
02:48:35,000 --> 02:48:38,600
Strange creatures bearing the White Hand
have been seen on our borders.

1508
02:48:39,100 --> 02:48:43,900
Seldom do Orcs journey in the open
under the sun, yet these have done so.

1509
02:48:52,800 --> 02:48:55,200
You are being tracked.

1510
02:48:56,800 --> 02:49:01,200
By river you have the chance of outrunning
the enemy to the Falls of Rauros.

1511
02:49:18,700 --> 02:49:23,300
My gift for you, Legolas,
is a bow of the Galadhrim.

1512
02:49:23,700 --> 02:49:27,000
Worthy of the skill
of our woodland kin.

1513
02:49:32,500 --> 02:49:34,800
These are the daggers of the Noldorin.

1514
02:49:35,200 --> 02:49:39,000
They have already seen service in war.

1515
02:49:39,300 --> 02:49:41,500
Do not fear, young Peregrin Took.

1516
02:49:41,800 --> 02:49:44,900
<i>You will find your courage.</i>

1517
02:49:47,000 --> 02:49:48,800
<i>And for you, Samwise Gamgee...</i>

1518
02:49:49,100 --> 02:49:51,500
...EIven rope made of hithlain.

1519
02:49:51,800 --> 02:49:53,900
Thank you, my lady.

1520
02:49:55,800 --> 02:49:59,000
Have you run out
of those nice, shiny daggers?

1521
02:50:05,600 --> 02:50:08,500
And what gift would a dwarf ask
of the Elves?

1522
02:50:08,800 --> 02:50:10,800
Nothing.

1523
02:50:11,500 --> 02:50:14,700
Except to look upon the lady
of the Galadhrim one last time...

1524
02:50:15,500 --> 02:50:20,500
...for she is more fair
than all the jewels beneath the earth.

1525
02:50:27,800 --> 02:50:29,200
Actually...

1526
02:50:29,600 --> 02:50:31,100
There was one thing.

1527
02:50:32,000 --> 02:50:34,500
No, no, I couldn't.
It's quite impossible.

1528
02:50:34,800 --> 02:50:37,500
<i>Stupid to ask.</i>

1529
02:50:40,200 --> 02:50:42,100
<i>I have nothing greater to give...</i>

1530
02:50:42,500 --> 02:50:45,900
...than the gift you already bear.

1531
02:50:47,300 --> 02:50:48,300
For her love,

1532
02:50:49,600 --> 02:50:54,800
I fear the grace of Arwen Evenstar
will diminish.

1533
02:50:55,700 --> 02:50:58,900
I would have her leave these shores,

1534
02:51:00,600 --> 02:51:03,300
and be with her people.

1535
02:51:05,500 --> 02:51:10,900
I would have her take the ship to Valinor.

1536
02:51:11,500 --> 02:51:14,400
That choice is yet before her.

1537
02:51:15,300 --> 02:51:18,000
You have your own choice to make,
Aragorn.

1538
02:51:18,600 --> 02:51:24,100
To rise above the height of all
your fathers since the days of Elendil...

1539
02:51:24,500 --> 02:51:28,700
...or to fall into darkness
with all that is left of your kin.

1540
02:51:36,100 --> 02:51:37,400
Farewell.

1541
02:51:41,300 --> 02:51:44,500
There is much you have yet to do.

1542
02:51:51,200 --> 02:51:52,400
We shall not meet again...

1543
02:51:52,700 --> 02:51:54,000
Elessar.

1544
02:51:56,400 --> 02:51:59,400
<i>Farewell, Frodo Baggins.</i>

1545
02:51:59,900 --> 02:52:03,100
I give you the light of Erendil...

1546
02:52:04,000 --> 02:52:06,200
...our most beloved star.

1547
02:52:15,500 --> 02:52:19,700
<i>May it be a light for you</i>
<i>in dark places...</i>

1548
02:52:20,100 --> 02:52:24,000
<i>...when all other lights go out.</i>

1549
02:52:33,200 --> 02:52:36,200
I have taken my worst wound
at this parting...

1550
02:52:37,000 --> 02:52:41,100
...having looked my last upon that
which is fairest.

1551
02:52:42,000 --> 02:52:45,200
Henceforth I will call nothing fair
unless it be her gift to me.

1552
02:52:45,600 --> 02:52:47,400
What was her gift?

1553
02:52:47,700 --> 02:52:52,400
I asked her for one hair
from her golden head.

1554
02:52:53,400 --> 02:52:56,100
She gave me three.

1555
02:54:38,500 --> 02:54:41,700
Gollum. He has tracked us since Moria.

1556
02:54:45,600 --> 02:54:48,600
I had hoped we would lose him
on the river.

1557
02:54:49,000 --> 02:54:52,100
But he's too clever a waterman.

1558
02:54:53,000 --> 02:54:56,100
And if he alerts the enemy
to our whereabouts...

1559
02:54:56,500 --> 02:54:58,600
...it will make the crossing
even more dangerous.

1560
02:54:58,900 --> 02:55:00,900
Have some food, Mr. Frodo.

1561
02:55:01,100 --> 02:55:04,000
- No, Sam.
- You haven't eaten anything all day.

1562
02:55:04,400 --> 02:55:07,400
You're not sleeping, neither.
Don't think I haven't noticed.

1563
02:55:08,400 --> 02:55:11,200
- Mr. Frodo...
- I'm all right.

1564
02:55:11,700 --> 02:55:12,800
But you're not.

1565
02:55:13,100 --> 02:55:15,400
I'm here to help you.

1566
02:55:15,800 --> 02:55:17,400
I promised Gandalf that I would.

1567
02:55:23,500 --> 02:55:26,100
You can't help me, Sam.

1568
02:55:28,400 --> 02:55:30,100
Not this time.

1569
02:55:32,900 --> 02:55:35,000
Get some sleep.

1570
02:55:41,300 --> 02:55:43,400
Minas Tirith is the safer road.

1571
02:55:44,100 --> 02:55:46,700
You know that.
From there we can regroup.

1572
02:55:47,500 --> 02:55:49,600
Strike out for Mordor from a place
of strength.

1573
02:55:50,000 --> 02:55:52,700
There is no strength in Gondor
that can avail us.

1574
02:55:53,400 --> 02:55:55,300
You were quick enough to trust
the Elves.

1575
02:55:57,200 --> 02:55:59,800
Have you so little faith
in your own people?

1576
02:56:00,300 --> 02:56:03,100
Yes, there is weakness.
There is frailty.

1577
02:56:03,400 --> 02:56:06,600
But there is courage also,
and honor to be found in Men.

1578
02:56:06,900 --> 02:56:09,000
But you will not see that.

1579
02:56:09,400 --> 02:56:10,800
You are afraid!

1580
02:56:11,100 --> 02:56:13,600
All your life, you have hidden
in the shadows.

1581
02:56:14,000 --> 02:56:17,300
Scared of who you are,
of what you are.

1582
02:56:19,900 --> 02:56:24,100
I will not lead the Ring within
a hundred leagues of your city.

1583
02:56:36,100 --> 02:56:37,300
Frodo.

1584
02:56:39,200 --> 02:56:40,700
The Argonath.

1585
02:56:44,300 --> 02:56:47,800
Long have I desired
to look upon the kings of old.

1586
02:56:48,700 --> 02:56:50,500
My kin.

1587
02:58:09,600 --> 02:58:11,700
We cross the lake at nightfall.

1588
02:58:12,000 --> 02:58:14,500
Hide the boats and continue on foot.

1589
02:58:14,800 --> 02:58:18,100
- We approach Mordor from the North.
- Oh, yes?

1590
02:58:18,700 --> 02:58:22,300
Just a simple matter of finding
our way through Emyn Muil...

1591
02:58:22,700 --> 02:58:25,800
...an impassable labyrinth
of razor-sharp rocks.

1592
02:58:26,100 --> 02:58:29,100
And after that, it gets even better.

1593
02:58:29,700 --> 02:58:34,300
Festering, stinking marshland
as far as the eye can see.

1594
02:58:34,800 --> 02:58:36,100
That is our road.

1595
02:58:37,700 --> 02:58:40,700
I suggest you take some rest
and recover your strength, Master Dwarf.

1596
02:58:41,000 --> 02:58:42,700
Recover my...

1597
02:58:45,800 --> 02:58:47,700
- We should leave now.
- No.

1598
02:58:48,000 --> 02:58:52,200
Orcs patrol the eastern shore.
We must wait for cover of darkness.

1599
02:58:52,600 --> 02:58:55,900
It is not the eastern shore
that worries me.

1600
02:58:56,200 --> 02:59:00,100
A shadow and a threat
has been growing in my mind.

1601
02:59:00,800 --> 02:59:04,800
Something draws near.
I can feel it.

1602
02:59:07,000 --> 02:59:11,700
Recover strength?
Pay no heed to that, young Hobbit.

1603
02:59:12,400 --> 02:59:14,000
Where's Frodo?

1604
02:59:39,800 --> 02:59:41,600
None of us should wander alone.

1605
02:59:43,000 --> 02:59:45,000
You, least of all.

1606
02:59:45,400 --> 02:59:47,700
So much depends on you.

1607
02:59:48,900 --> 02:59:50,800
Frodo?

1608
02:59:58,000 --> 03:00:00,500
I know why you seek solitude.

1609
03:00:01,300 --> 03:00:04,500
You suffer. I see it day by day.

1610
03:00:05,500 --> 03:00:08,400
You sure you do not suffer needlessly?

1611
03:00:10,100 --> 03:00:12,700
There are other ways, Frodo.

1612
03:00:13,100 --> 03:00:16,700
- Other paths that we might take.
- I know what you would say.

1613
03:00:17,100 --> 03:00:20,700
It would seem like wisdom
but for the warning in my heart.

1614
03:00:21,100 --> 03:00:24,000
Warning? Against what?

1615
03:00:24,400 --> 03:00:26,400
We're all afraid, Frodo.

1616
03:00:26,700 --> 03:00:30,200
But to let that fear drive us,
to destroy what hope we have...

1617
03:00:30,600 --> 03:00:34,200
...don't you see that is madness?
- There is no other way.

1618
03:00:36,100 --> 03:00:39,300
I ask only for the strength
to defend my people!

1619
03:00:41,000 --> 03:00:43,000
- Lf you would but lend me the Ring.
- No.

1620
03:00:44,300 --> 03:00:47,800
- Why do you recoil? I am no thief.
- You are not yourself.

1621
03:00:49,800 --> 03:00:53,000
What chance do you think you have?

1622
03:00:53,300 --> 03:00:57,800
They will find you.
They will take the Ring.

1623
03:00:58,200 --> 03:01:01,700
And you will beg for death
before the end!

1624
03:01:04,000 --> 03:01:06,000
You fool!

1625
03:01:06,300 --> 03:01:10,100
It is not yours, save by unhappy chance!
It could have been mine.

1626
03:01:10,500 --> 03:01:13,200
It should be mine! Give it to me!

1627
03:01:13,500 --> 03:01:14,700
- Give it to me!
- No!

1628
03:01:15,000 --> 03:01:16,700
- Give it to me!
- No.

1629
03:01:24,500 --> 03:01:26,400
I see your mind.

1630
03:01:26,700 --> 03:01:29,500
You will take the Ring to Sauron!

1631
03:01:29,900 --> 03:01:31,600
You will betray us!

1632
03:01:32,000 --> 03:01:35,000
You'll go to your death,
and the death of us all!

1633
03:01:35,500 --> 03:01:39,000
Curse you!
Curse you and all the halflings!

1634
03:01:46,300 --> 03:01:47,800
Frodo?

1635
03:01:52,100 --> 03:01:53,600
Frodo.

1636
03:01:57,600 --> 03:01:59,500
What have I done?

1637
03:01:59,900 --> 03:02:01,500
Please, Frodo.

1638
03:02:01,800 --> 03:02:04,400
Frodo, I'm sorry!

1639
03:02:53,100 --> 03:02:54,400
Frodo?

1640
03:02:55,700 --> 03:02:58,700
- It has taken Boromir.
- Where is the Ring?

1641
03:02:59,000 --> 03:03:00,700
Stay away!

1642
03:03:01,200 --> 03:03:02,700
Frodo!

1643
03:03:05,100 --> 03:03:08,700
- I swore to protect you.
- Can you protect me from yourself?

1644
03:03:18,500 --> 03:03:20,900
Would you destroy it?

1645
03:03:26,000 --> 03:03:27,900
<i>Aragorn.</i>

1646
03:03:31,500 --> 03:03:33,700
<i>Aragorn.</i>

1647
03:03:35,500 --> 03:03:37,300
<i>Elessar.</i>

1648
03:03:45,000 --> 03:03:48,300
I would have gone with you to the end.

1649
03:03:49,100 --> 03:03:51,800
Into the very fires of Mordor.

1650
03:03:55,200 --> 03:03:56,300
I know.

1651
03:03:58,900 --> 03:04:04,100
Look after the others. Especially Sam.
He will not understand.

1652
03:04:08,200 --> 03:04:09,800
Go, Frodo!

1653
03:04:12,800 --> 03:04:14,200
Run.

1654
03:04:14,600 --> 03:04:16,100
Run!

1655
03:04:40,800 --> 03:04:42,400
Mr. Frodo!

1656
03:04:51,700 --> 03:04:53,400
Find the halfling!

1657
03:04:55,200 --> 03:04:57,600
Find the halfling!

1658
03:05:01,100 --> 03:05:02,700
Elendil!

1659
03:05:09,300 --> 03:05:10,700
Aragorn, go!

1660
03:05:32,600 --> 03:05:33,800
Frodo!

1661
03:05:34,500 --> 03:05:36,000
Hide here. Quick!

1662
03:05:36,800 --> 03:05:38,100
Come on!

1663
03:05:40,600 --> 03:05:42,600
What's he doing?

1664
03:05:46,900 --> 03:05:48,800
He's leaving.

1665
03:05:53,700 --> 03:05:56,500
- No!
- Pippin!

1666
03:06:01,600 --> 03:06:03,800
Run, Frodo. Go on!

1667
03:06:04,400 --> 03:06:07,400
- Hey! Hey, you!
- Over here!

1668
03:06:07,900 --> 03:06:09,400
- Over here!
- This way!

1669
03:06:20,300 --> 03:06:22,600
- It's working!
- I know it's working! Run!

1670
03:07:18,100 --> 03:07:21,000
- The horn of Gondor.
- Boromir.

1671
03:08:04,200 --> 03:08:05,300
Run!

1672
03:11:36,900 --> 03:11:38,500
No.

1673
03:11:42,500 --> 03:11:45,400
- They took the little ones.
- Hold still.

1674
03:11:45,700 --> 03:11:47,700
Frodo. Where is Frodo?

1675
03:11:49,700 --> 03:11:51,100
I let Frodo go.

1676
03:11:51,800 --> 03:11:54,300
Then you did what I could not.

1677
03:11:55,400 --> 03:11:58,500
I tried to take the Ring from him.

1678
03:11:59,300 --> 03:12:03,300
- The Ring is beyond our reach now.
- Forgive me.

1679
03:12:03,700 --> 03:12:05,800
I did not see it.

1680
03:12:06,300 --> 03:12:09,300
- I have failed you all.
- No, Boromir.

1681
03:12:09,800 --> 03:12:12,300
You fought bravely.

1682
03:12:12,700 --> 03:12:15,200
You have kept your honor.

1683
03:12:15,900 --> 03:12:17,700
Leave it.

1684
03:12:18,100 --> 03:12:20,100
It is over.

1685
03:12:21,500 --> 03:12:26,500
The world of Men will fall.
And all will come to darkness...

1686
03:12:27,100 --> 03:12:30,000
...and my city to ruin.

1687
03:12:34,200 --> 03:12:36,800
I do not know what strength
is in my blood...

1688
03:12:37,100 --> 03:12:40,900
...but I swear to you,
I will not let the White City fall...

1689
03:12:42,100 --> 03:12:44,500
...nor our people fail.

1690
03:12:45,600 --> 03:12:46,900
Our people.

1691
03:12:50,800 --> 03:12:52,800
Our people.

1692
03:13:14,600 --> 03:13:17,500
I would have followed you, my brother.

1693
03:13:19,200 --> 03:13:21,100
My captain.

1694
03:13:23,800 --> 03:13:25,600
My king.

1695
03:13:45,400 --> 03:13:47,500
Be at peace...

1696
03:13:48,000 --> 03:13:49,900
...son of Gondor.

1697
03:14:06,500 --> 03:14:09,700
They will look for his coming
from the White Tower.

1698
03:14:10,300 --> 03:14:13,200
But he will not return.

1699
03:14:36,600 --> 03:14:38,500
Frodo!

1700
03:14:58,000 --> 03:15:01,200
<i>I wish the Ring had never come to me.</i>

1701
03:15:02,500 --> 03:15:05,300
<i>I wish none of this had happened.</i>

1702
03:15:08,500 --> 03:15:11,100
<i>So do all who live</i>
<i>to see such times...</i>

1703
03:15:11,400 --> 03:15:14,700
<i>...but that is not for them to decide.</i>

1704
03:15:15,200 --> 03:15:17,700
<i>All you have to decide...</i>

1705
03:15:18,000 --> 03:15:22,500
...is what to do with the time
that is given to you.

1706
03:15:51,500 --> 03:15:53,500
Frodo, no!

1707
03:15:54,100 --> 03:15:55,300
Frodo!

1708
03:15:56,200 --> 03:15:58,800
- Mr. Frodo!
- No, Sam.

1709
03:16:02,500 --> 03:16:04,300
Go back, Sam!

1710
03:16:04,900 --> 03:16:08,300
- I'm going to Mordor alone.
- Of course you are.

1711
03:16:08,700 --> 03:16:11,400
And I'm coming with you!

1712
03:16:12,100 --> 03:16:14,400
You can't swim!

1713
03:16:18,200 --> 03:16:19,800
Sam!

1714
03:16:25,500 --> 03:16:26,800
Sam!

1715
03:17:07,700 --> 03:17:10,300
I made a promise, Mr. Frodo.

1716
03:17:10,900 --> 03:17:15,000
A promise:
"Don't you leave him, Samwise Gamgee."

1717
03:17:16,300 --> 03:17:18,800
And I don't mean to.

1718
03:17:19,200 --> 03:17:21,200
I don't mean to.

1719
03:17:23,000 --> 03:17:24,800
Sam.

1720
03:17:40,000 --> 03:17:41,600
Come on.

1721
03:18:10,200 --> 03:18:14,500
Hurry! Frodo and Sam
have reached the eastern shore.

1722
03:18:29,600 --> 03:18:34,400
- You mean not to follow them.
- Frodo's fate is no longer in our hands.

